name: Sterling, Brass & Copper House Studs
description:
Spot the difference! A pair of slightly mismatched Sterling studs with textured metals and patination to add interest and subtlety.

Approx 1cm square, Sterling with copper and brass, sterling posts and butterflies. 

Code 159

name: Round Stripey Silver Studs
description:
Hooray for stripes.

A rare foray into the world of studs, and away from the beloved danglers - but still mismatched.

7mm in diameter with my trademark etching - subtle but still different from the usual.

Sterling silver, on sterling silver posts and backs.

name: 158 Rolled & Patinated Sterling Silver Studs
description:
I had a lot of fun making these!  

Sterling Silver is etched and rolled, to create patterns and textures inspired by the landscape, wire fencing, and plant tendrils.  I then polish and patinate to add further interest and depth to the design, with the patination giving a beautiful warm colour to contrast with the polished silver.  The piece is then lacquered to protect this effect.   

No two are the same, and the pair is deliberately mismatched.  The pair you receive will be of the same design and size, but will not be exactly the same as pictured as all are unique.

Approx 1.2cm square, Sterling Silver with Sterling posts and butterflies.

name: 106 Square Etched Studs
description:
Each earring different in these square studs, one of my more subtle and sophisticated offerings!  Perfect for a bit of everyday interest, each is individually etched with patterns and textures inspired by the landscape. To finish, I patinate and polish to create a contrast which brings out the design.

Approx 1cm square Sterling Silver with sterling posts and butterflies.

name: Sterling Silver Embossed & Patinated Square Studs
description:
Deliberately mismatched sterling silver stud earrings depicting a house and moon.  

Rolled through my lovely rolling mill using my own etched plates, and carefully patinated to bring out the design and add interest.  They are then lacquered to ensure the patination is not damaged.

These are made individually to order so will not be exactly the same as pictured, but this makes them totally unique! 

Measure 1.2 x 1.2 cm with sterling silver post and butterfies.

name: Landscape Copper & Enamel Studs
description:
Square Sterling Studs with copper shapes inspired by the landscape.  

A couple of layers of beautiful transparent vitreous enamel in blues and greys are added to give a contrast to the warm copper tone.  Intentionally mismatched, no two are the same.

Approx 1 x 1 cm Sterling Silver with copper.  Sterling posts and butterflies. 

Code 109

name: Enamelled disc studs
description:
A pair of subtly coloured little domed enamelled discs.  

Several layers of beautiful transparent vitreous enamel colours are built up over domed discs of silver in successive kiln firings to create a subtle colour effect, which varies from pair to pair.  Colours vary from blues to greens with smatterings of gold and grey. Rim is polished silver to contrast with the colour.         

Approx 0.8cm diameter Sterling Silver with Sterling posts and butterflies.

name: Doorknob Danglers
description:
Rolled and Patinated drop earrings with a really simple, high contrast design.  

The little copper rivet doorknobs add a touch of colour and mean these earrings can be worn with a variety of accessories.  I wear mine all the time!

Sterling silver & copper, on handmade sterling wires. Approx 1 x 2 cm not including wires.

Code 119

name: Long Etched Silver Danglers
description:
One of my more sophisticated and understated designs I feel! I do love a stripe.

Etched silver earrings with a really lovely contrast of shine and patination.

On sterling silver earwires. Drop approx 5cm

These are made individually to order so will not be exactly the same as pictured, but this all adds to their uniqueness!

name: Silver & Copper Bird & Moon Earrings
description:
I love the way the etching turned out on these! 

Silver and copper etched mismatched earrings. 

Silver abstract landscape or tree background, one with moon and the other with bird, in copper. 

These are smaller and more delicate than a lot of my earrings, for people who like things small and delicate.  0.5 x 3cm.

Ref 58a

name: Multicoloured Semi-Precious Earrings
description:
These look so lovely when they catch the light!

Faceted and smooth Garnet, Freshwater Pearl, Labradorite & Agate are used in different combinations and colours with handmade silver or copper wire designs, to make a lovely 'same but different' pair of earrings.

4cm drop including handmade sterling earwires and large sterling jump rings.

Ref 214

name: Monochrome Earrings
description:
Matching Silver, black and grey earrings contrasting matt black textured lava stone, shiny metallic grey haematite and the beautifully subtle grey/blue sheen of Labradorite.  A combination of copper and silver handmade spirals hold the whole thing together and the copper gives it a splash of colour.  

Also available in an all-silver matching option, shown in picture 2, using haematite, faceted black agate and grey freshwater pearls.

Perfect for everyday or dressing up, and will go with everything. I love these earrings, even though they match!

Drop Approx 3.5cm including handmade sterling earwires.

Ref 237

options.name: Matching monochrome all silver and pearl

name: Silver Tree Disc & Lava Earrings
description:
A disc of silver etched with an abstract, almost runic tree pattern.  

Mismatched with Matt black textured Lava on a handmade silver spiral and hanging on antiqued belcher chain.

Drop approx 5cm including handmade Sterling earwires.

name: Enamelled Bird Pendant
description:
This chap has his beady eye on you!

Many layers of beautiful transparent vitreous enamel are built up on top of this etched silver design to create a subtle effect that is different in every piece.  

Real gold leaf is embedded to give a contrast to the blues and greens in the wing.  Finished off with a copper or brass riveted eye (depending on my mood at the time!).

Approx 2 x 4cm max. Sterling Silver, Gold leaf & enamel on Sterling Snake chain (please specify size when ordering) 

Code 161

name: Sterling Domed Moon Pendant
description:
A little bit Barbara Hepworth, a little bit Samuel Palmer (or am I getting ideas above my station?!)

Domed Sterling Silver pendant with contrasting polished and patinated & engraved surfaces.  Lovely and simple, this looks lovely on a Sterling Silver snake chain or handmade tendril Sterling choker (please specify when ordering).

Approx 2cm diameter.

Code 152

name: Long Sterling Landscape Pendant
description:
Etched houses and moon on an etched landscape, all patinated and polished for extra contrast.  

Approx 4cm x 1cm Sterling Silver on Sterling snake chain.  Please specify length when ordering. 

Code 141

name: Silver Landscape Pendant with cutout Moon
description:
A landscape pendant in landscape format!

Simple abstract design - etched background with more highly polished etched strip to contrast and cutout moon, inspired by Henry Moore - makes a change from Samuel Palmer!

Attached by 2 jump rings to antiqued Sterling Silver belcher chain. Measures 3.8 x 2cm.

Ref:60

name: Moongazing Hare Pendant
description:
Inspired by English folklore and folk songs, this pendant uses etched and patinated Sterling Silver to recreate the patterns and textures of the landscape.  The etched hare stares at a silver moon (luckily there are no copper foxes in sight tonight). 

Approx 2 x 4cm Sterling Silver with sterling findings and sterling snake chain, please specify length when ordering.

Code 142

name: Seagull Pendant
description:
Avast Me Hearties!  This highly polished silver seagull soars above a storm-tossed sea.

With textures and colours inspired by the seascape and created using traditional etching and patination techniques, no two pieces will ever be the same. 

Approx 2 x 4cm. All Sterling Silver, on Sterling snake chain.  Please specify length when ordering. 

Code 143

name: Silver Landscape & Copper Houses Etched Pendant
description:
A landscape scene with a moon shining above a landscape with a row of little copper houses below.

Etched and patinated, on sterling silver snake chain. 2.3 x 3cm.


Ref:61c

name: Cut Out Bird in Tree Copper & Silver Pendant
description:
Bird + Tree = Marvellous

I like to think this tree is a little bit Tolkienesque (I said a little bit).  Hand etched and painstakingly cut out copper (I don't usually do painstaking) with a little Sterling silver etched bird perched in its branches.

Measures 4 x 4.5cm, with 2 sterling silver jumprings on steel memory wire choker.

The two pictures are of necklaces which are already sold, but I can make more (not exactly the same, of course).  Please contact me for lead times (usually around 2 weeks).

name: Copper & Silver Dangly House
description:
A lovely dangly little abode.  Etched and patinated copper and sterling silver dangle on a copper-coloured memory wire choker. This can be changed for sterling silver snake chain as an optional extra.

All are slightly different. If you have a preference, please let me know, otherwise I will send the one in the first picture.

I can also put a number on the house door (max 2 digits) for a personalised touch.

Ref:048, 049, 051

name: Silvery Moon
description:
A digital print of a detail taken from one of my etched silver pendants. 

Enlarged and colour-enhanced to bring out the subtle tones of the silver. 

Sold unframed and unmounted (but fits nicely in a standard square frame). Signed Edition of 100.  Image size 10cm x 10cm.

Please note picture for illustration purposes only - frame and mount not included.

name: Moonlit Landscape Wood Engraving
description:
A wood engraving of a house in a moonlit landscape.  Wood engraving is much more precise and usually smaller scale than woodcut, with the end grain wood being used.  Lots of different mark-making techniques create the effects of the landscape in what I like to think is quite an atmospheric print!  

Each one is individually hand printed onto good quality paper using lovely black letterpress ink.  Signed.  Linited Edition of 50.

Image size 7.5 x 7.5cm.  Sold unframed and unmounted but fits nicely in a standard square frame.  Edition shown is 1/50 but obviously when this is sold, number will change according to edition number.
